{
  "stem": "10572.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was another unbelievable thing that is staying with me until the day I die.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The-- the [NON-ENGLISH] was the main gate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And-- and whenever you were called for something horrible or good, for your release, you were called to the main gate to [NON-ENGLISH] And it had all kinds of connotations, horror or good news.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And one day, the monotone public address system that would constantly call out names, the numbers, they called out my name.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I couldn't believe that maybe I was on the way to freedom.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And there was a small group.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I think we were maybe 25 guys standing there who were ready to be released.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And on one side of the main gate, there were cells, solitary cells, for people with famous names who were ready to be sent to-- before they were sent to the crematorium so that they could be handled individually.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And in one of the small cells, while we were standing there waiting to be released, we heard the smashing of a window and a desperate voice screaming, screaming at us and saying, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And it was a Protestant pastor, Pastor Schneider, who, in defiance to his captors, screamed at us, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And the words were stilled.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And Pastor Schneider was dead.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They killed him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Martin Zimmer, who was the SS man who was in charge of those individual cells, took care of people like that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And Margie and I, many, many years later in 1974, Margie and I went back to Buchenwald with a friend of mine.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And there is today, in the cell, there is a chapel with a huge cross in memory of Pastor Schneider, who was killed at the moment when I was ready to return to freedom.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A little bit less than three months.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
